      <h2>Why the Grocery List Matters More Than the Tracking</h2>

      <p>
        You can't track what isn't there. Most men fail to hit 120g not because they forget to log — but because they open the fridge at noon and there's nothing high-protein to reach for. A stocked kitchen removes the decision. You log what you ate. You don't have to engineer a high-protein meal from nothing.
      </p>

      <p>
        The tracking just makes the gap visible. <a href="https://snapprotein.com/blog/hard-to-hit-protein-goal-after-40/">The reason hitting 120g is hard after 40</a> isn't effort — it's that most men don't know where they stand until the day is over. That's a visibility problem, not a willpower problem. Solve the grocery list, solve the kitchen, then use tracking to confirm you got there.
      </p>

